name: 2,6-dimethoxybenzoyl chloride
Reason: 2,6-dimethoxybenzoyl chloride has a basic unit of benzene, which has a melting point of 5.5°C. The methoxy groups are known to increase the melting point due to increased molecular weight and hydrogen bonding capabilities.
